caption;Versi 2
no;1
p;Oh, spread the tidings ’round, wherever man is found,
p;Wherever human hearts and human woes abound;
p;Let every Christian tongue proclaim the joyful sound:
p;The Comforter has come!
empty
no;ref
pi;The Comforter has come, the Comforter has come!
pi;The Holy Ghost from Heav’n, the Father’s promise giv’n;
pi;Oh, spread the tidings ’round, wherever man is found—
pi;The Comforter has come!
empty
no;2
p;The long, long night is past, the morning breaks at last,
p;And hushed the dreadful wail and fury of the blast,
p;As o’er the golden hills the day advances fast!
p;The Comforter has come!
empty
no;3
p;Lo, the great King of kings, with healing in His wings,
p;To every captive soul a full deliv’rance brings;
p;And through the vacant cells the song of triumph rings;
p;The Comforter has come!
empty
no;4
p;O boundless love divine! How shall this tongue of mine
p;To wond’ring mortals tell the matchless grace divine—
p;That I, a child of hell, should in His image shine!
p;The Comforter has come!
